#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to solve this issue"
msgstr "Probleemi lahendamise võimalused:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:38
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If the application is &kde; software, start by searching the <ulink url="
#| "\"http://docs.kde.org/\">KDE Documentation site</ulink> for the requested "
#| "documentation. If you find the documentation on that site, your "
#| "distribution might ship a separate package for documentation (&eg; called "
#| "plasma-doc for documentation related to &plasma;). Please use the package "
#| "manager of your distribution to find and install the missing "
#| "documentation."
msgid ""
"If the application is &kde; software, first use the search function in "
"&khelpcenter;. In some cases, the documentation has a different name than "
"the software was using to try to find it. If that doesn't work, try "
"searching the <ulink url=\"https://docs.kde.org/\">&kde; Documentation site</"
"ulink> for the requested documentation. If you find the documentation on "
"that site, your distribution might ship a separate package for documentation "
"(&eg; called plasma-doc for documentation related to &plasma;). Please use "
"the package manager of your distribution to find and install the missing "
"documentation."
msgstr ""
"Kui tegemist on &kde; tarkvaraga, alusta soovitud dokumentatsiooni "
"otsimisega <ulink url=\"http://docs.kde.org/\">KDE dokumentatsiooni "
"veebileheküljelt</ulink>. Kui leiad selle sealt, siis on võib-olla sinu "
"distributsioon pakendanud dokumentatsiooni eraldi paketina (nt. plasma-doc "
"&plasma;ga seotud dokumentatsiooni tarbeks). Sel juhul kasuta oma "
"distributsiooni tarkvarahaldurit ja otsi sealt vajalik "
"dokumentatsioonipakett üles."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you use a source based distribution, such as Gentoo, be sure that there "
"are not any configuration settings (USE flags in Gentoo) that might have "
"disabled the installation of the documentation."
msgstr ""
"Kui kasutada mõnda lähtekoodipõhist distributsiooni, näiteks Gentood, "
"kontrolli, kas pole mõnda seadistust (USE lipud Gentoos), mis võivad "
"takistada dokumentatsiooni paigaldamist."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:53
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you have done that, but still get this page displayed instead of the "
#| "application handbook, you probably found a bug in the help system. In "
#| "this case, please report this on the <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/"
#| "\">KDE Bug Tracker</ulink> under the KIO product."
msgid ""
"If you have done that, but still get this page displayed instead of the "
"application handbook, you probably found a bug in the help system. In this "
"case, please report this on the <ulink url=\"https://bugs.kde.org/\">&kde;'s "
"bugtracker</ulink> under the KIO product."
msgstr ""
"Kui ka pärast seda ei ilmu rakenduse käsiraamat nähtavale, oled arvatavasti "
"leidnud vea abisüsteemis. Sel juhul anna palun sellest teada <ulink url="
"\"http://bugs.kde.org/\">KDE vigade jälgimise süsteemis</ulink>, valides "
"\"tooteks\" (product) KIO."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:59
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you do not find any documentation on the <ulink url=\"http://docs.kde."
#| "org/\">KDE Documentation site</ulink>, the application may not have "
#| "offline documentation. Please report this on the <ulink url=\"http://bugs."
#| "kde.org/\">KDE Bug Tracker</ulink> under the product for the application."
msgid ""
"If you do not find any documentation on the <ulink url=\"https://docs.kde."
"org/\">&kde; Documentation site</ulink>, the application may not have "
"offline documentation. Please report this on the <ulink url=\"https://bugs."
"kde.org/\">&kde;'s bugtracker</ulink> under the product for the application."
msgstr ""
"Kui sa ei leia dokumentatsiooni <ulink url=\"http://docs.kde.org/\">KDE "
"dokumentatsiooni veebileheküljelt</ulink>, võib see tähendada, et rakendusel "
"polegi käsiraamatut. Sel juhul anna sellest teada <ulink url=\"http://bugs."
"kde.org/\">KDE vigade jälgimise süsteemis</ulink>, valides \"tooteks"
"\" (product) vastava rakenduse."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:66
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In case the application does not have offline documentation, you should "
#| "use the online resources <ulink url=\"http://userbase.kde.org/\">UserBase "
#| "Documentation</ulink> and <ulink url=\"http://forum.kde.org/\">KDE "
#| "Community Forums</ulink> to get help."
msgid ""
"In case the application does not have offline documentation, you should use "
"the online resources <ulink url=\"https://userbase.kde.org/\">UserBase "
"Documentation</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://forum.kde.org/\">&kde; "
"Community Forums</ulink> to get help."
msgstr ""
"Kui rakendusel puudub käsiraamat, kasuta abi hankimiseks ressursse, mida "
"pakuvad <ulink url=\"http://userbase.kde.org/\">UserBase'i dokumentatsioon</"
"ulink> ja <ulink url=\"http://forum.kde.org/\">KDE kogukonna foorumid</"
"ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For non-&kde; applications, please contact the application author to "
"determine whether there should be offline documentation available."
msgstr ""
"&kde;-väliste rakenduse korral võta palun ühendust rakenduse autoriga, et "
"saada teada, kas rakendusele peabki üldse olema omaette dokumentatsiooni."

